Former President Goodluck Jonathan has mourned Jerry Rawlings. The former President of Ghana died on Thursday at Korle-Bu Teaching Hospital in Accra. In a statement, Jonathan extended his condolences to the government and people of Ghana. He said as Ghana’s leader, the deceased acquitted himself as a soldier of the masses and crusader for social justice. Jonathan called Rawlings a courageous statesman and a great Pan-Africanist with strong views and drive for the continent’s renaissance and growth. “He died at a time the continent needed his wisdom and experience to deal with challenging socio-political issues”, the statement read. The former Nigerian leader prayed God to grant Rawlings’s soul eternal rest.